    thinking: "**Refining Imports for Dashboard**\n\nI\'m currently updating the `UserDashboard.tsx` imports, and integrating `useState` along with essential icons like `User`, `Utensils`, `Dumbbell`, and `TrendingUp`. I\'m using `multi_edit_file` to handle the modifications. I\'ve got the import section refined now, and this is the first phase of the update to be implemented.\n\n\n**Expanding Imports Further**\n\nI\'m now integrating even more imports into `UserDashboard.tsx`. I\'ve added icons like `CalendarCheck`, `MessageSquare`, `CreditCard`, `LogOut`, `Menu`, `X`, `Send`, `Upload`, and `Loader2`. I\'m also including imports for `Link` from `react-router-dom`, and components for a line chart from `recharts`. The code includes imports for `GoogleGenAI` and `Type` from `@google/genai` to enable GenAI integration.\nI\'m also setting the state using useState for `activeTab`, `isSidebarOpen`, `profile`, `dietPlan`, `isGenerating`, and `error`. I\'ve created the `generateDietPlan` function with `async` and `await`, to set `setIsGenerating(true)`.\n\n\n**Implementing Diet Plan Logic**\n\nI\'m now diving into the core logic for diet plan generation. I\'m leveraging `GoogleGenAI` to formulate the plan based on user profile details like age, gender, weight, height, goal, and activity level. The process utilizes `async` and `await` with `ai.models.generateContent` to request a personalized plan. I\'m specifically setting the `responseMimeType` to `application/json`, which I\'ll be using to parse the data from the diet plan generated.\n\n\n**Parsing Diet Plan Response**\n\nI\'m now focusing on parsing the diet plan response. I\'ve integrated a JSON schema validation within `generateDietPlan` for handling the `application/json` response and parsing it with a defined structure. The code includes validation for calories, macros, meals (including names, descriptions, and calories), and a grocery list. I\'m handling potential errors to set an error state, and ensuring `setIsGenerating` is set to false, regardless of success or failure. I have also added logic to show profile tab.\n\n\n**Adding Profile Logic**\n\nI\'m now integrating the profile setup section within `UserDashboard.tsx`, including input fields for age and a select dropdown for gender, both updating the `profile` state using `useState`. I\'m setting up error handling for invalid input and updating the UI accordingly. I\'m leveraging Tailwind classes for styling and layout and ensuring a clean user experience.\n\n\n**Enhancing Profile Input**\n\nI\'m currently working to expand the profile input fields within `UserDashboard.tsx`. I\'ve added fields for weight and height, handling numeric input and ensuring the values are stored correctly in the `profile` state. I\'m also styling these fields with Tailwind classes to maintain a consistent UI and a good user experience. I have incorporated error handling for input validation. I plan to enhance error messages further for more precise feedback.\n\n\n**Finalizing Profile Setup**\n\nI\'ve just added the \"Goal\" and \"Activity Level\" selection dropdowns to the profile setup in `UserDashboard.tsx`, completing the profile input section. These utilize `useState` to update the `profile` state. I\'ve used Tailwind for styling and validation for a user-friendly experience. Now I\'m preparing to test this comprehensively.\n\n\n"
